cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses distributed optimization for training large models on large datasets, which is a common topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses communication efficiency, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The experiments involve image classification and machine translation, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a new optimization framework, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
